frameDefinitions: The words in this frame describe situations in which the Perpetrator secretly takes Goods into or out of a country or other area which are prohibited by law or on which one has not paid the required duty.
An Importer receives Goods from an Exporting_area, across a boundary or border to a different area, the Importing_area.
An object Theme moves in the direction of a Goal.
An Agent cuts a Item into Pieces using an Instrument (which may or may not be expressed).
An Exporter moves Goods across a border from an Exporting_area to an Importing_area.
frameExamples: The U.S. <t>imported</t> some wheat in the period, although it exported about ten times as much.
Some students <t>arrived</t> at the school on Sunday.
At the ceremony, the CEO <t>cut</t> the red ribbon hanging across the main entrance into a glorious confetti.
Several companies actually make most of their income by <t>exporting</t> goods out of the country.
listRoleDefinitions: This is the person (or other agent) that illegally takes the goods into or out of a country.
The role Goods is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be illegally taken into our out of a country.
The source is the location the goods occupy initially before change of location.
The path refers to (a part of the) ground the Goods travel over or to a landmark the Goods travel by.
Goal is the location the Goods end up in.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that brings the <fen>Goods</fen> into the <fen>Importing_area</fen>.
The items of value whose location is changing.
The role <fen>Importing_area</fen> is the place that the <fen>Goods</fen> end up as a result of motion.
The place where the <fen>Goods</fen> are initially, before the being moved.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Importer</fen> moves the <fen>Goods</fen>.
<fen>Theme</fen> is the object that moves. It may be an entity that moves under its own power, but it need not be.
<fen>Goal</fen> is any expression that tells where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up, or would end up, as a result of the motion.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when arriving occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the arriving event occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person cutting the <fen>Item</fen> into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The item which is being cut into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The <fen>Pieces</fen> are the parts of the original <fen>Item</fen> which are the result of the slicing.
When the slicing occurs.
Where the slicing takes place.

The conscious entity, generally a person, that moves the <fen>Goods</fen> across a border out of the <fen>Exporting_area</fen>.  

Very often, an <fen>Exporting_area</fen> will metonymically stand in for the person or persons directly responsible for the movement of the <fen>Goods</fen>.  In such cases the constituent should be labeled <fen>Exporter</fen> on the first layer and with the appropriate locational role on the second layer.
The items of value whose location is changing.
The role <fen>Importing_area</fen> is the place that the <fen>Goods</fen> end up as a result of motion.
The place where the <fen>Goods</fen> are initially, before the the <fen>Exporter</fen> moves them.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Exporter</fen> moves the <fen>Goods</fen>.
listRoleExamples: People back then had to chop <fex>firewood</fex> all day long.
<fex>The U.S.</fex> exports most of its peanut products.
